Nd7 is not possible anymore.}) 12. O-O-O Nce5 $1 {And this is the "right
knight" to be on e5, as the rook will be actively placed on the c-file and the
idea Nb6-c4 is available.} 13. Kb1 {The most popular move, securing the king's
position.} (13. Nd4 Rc8 {, and White will have to think about the sacrifice on
c3 anyway.} 14. Qe3) 13... Rc8 14. Qe3 (14. Nd5 {looks like an easy way to get
a small positional advantage, but Black has no problems here.} Bxd5 15. exd5 (
15. Rxd5 O-O 16. g4 Nb6 17. Rd1 {Vehi Bach,V (2460)-Herrera,I (2478)/Peregrina
