Nxd3 19. Qxd3 Qxd3 20. cxd3 e6 $11 {Black is at least fine.}) 7... Bg7 8. f3
Nc6 9. Qd2 (9. Nxc6 bxc6 10. O-O {White plays this way hoping for a tiny
advantage, in view of his slightly better structure, but objectively Black is
