and wait, because after} 15. Nd5 Bxd5 16. exd5 Nc5 17. Nxc5 dxc5 18. c4 Bd6 {
[%cal Ye5e4] Black has nice chances of counterplay.} 19. b4 $6 Qe7 20. b5 e4 $1
{[%cal Ye8e1,Gd6h2]} 21. f4 axb5 22. cxb5 c4 $1 23. Rxc4 Rxc4 24. Bxc4 Ng4 $36
