{White just played Nf5. What's the best reaction for Black?} 18... Nb6 $1 {
[%cal Yb6c4] Looking to active counterplay on the queenside.} 19. Qd4 (19. Nxd6
$2 Bxd6 20. Rxd6 Nec4 $19) 19... Nec4 20. Bxc4 Nxc4 21. Nxd6 Nxa3+ $3 {A very
strong idea.} 22. bxa3 Rxc3 {[%csl Gb1,Re8] Black is losing the rook on e8,
but White should better think about king safety and play} 23. Qb4 (23. Nxe8 $2
Qxa3 {, and the only way to avoid mate in four is} 24. Qxc3 Qxc3 $19) 23...
Qxb4+ 24. axb4 Bxd6 25. Bxd6 Rec8 $15 {Navara,D (2751)-So,W (2778) Prague Cez
Trophy m 2015 (1) 1/2} *

