{What's the best idea for Black in this position?} 17... Bc4 $1 {The right way
to make use of the c4-square in this case.} ({After} 17... Nc4 $2 18. Nd5 {
White has no problems:} Bxd5 19. exd5 $14 {Black has lost all of his potential
on the queenside.}) 18. Bxc4 (18. Qd2 Bxb5 19. Nxb5 Qc4 $19) 18... Qxc4 19.
Qxc4 Rxc4 {[%csl Ya4] The pressure on a4 is a good reason to keep the knight.}
20. Nd2 $2 ({the correct is} 20. f3 $1 Nxa4 21. Nxa4 Rxa4 22. Rd5 {[%csl Ya5]}
b6 23. Nd2 $44) 20... Rxc3 $1 21. bxc3 Nxa4 $17 {[%csl Rc3] Black unavoidably
wins the second pawn for the exchange, with a clear advantage. Molina, R (2423)
-Mareco,S (2557) Albena Masters op 2013 (3) 0-1} *

