{This is a typical position from the lines in which White plays 6.Be3 and 10.
f4. What's the correct continuation for Black now?} 14... Nxe3 15. Qxe3 Bxb3 $1
{It is important to remember that this is the right exchange, due to two
reasons, the first being that the light-squared bishop is practically useless
for White's attacking purposes.} 16. Qh6 $2 (16. axb3 Kh8 17. Nd5 Nf6 18. Qg3
Rg8 {is nothing for White.}) 16... Bxc2+ $1 {This intermediate move is the
second and main reason behind Black's 15th move.} 17. Kxc2 Bf6 {Black is (at
least) a pawn up and the attack on the kingside can be easily repulsed.} 18.
Rxd6 (18. Rd3 Kh8 19. Qh5 h6 $1 20. Rh3 Kh7 $17) 18... Kh8 19. Qd2 Ra7 {
Black is already better.} 20. Kb1 Qc7 21. Rd3 Nb6 $17 {Nisipeanu,L (2668)
-Karjakin,S (2694) World Cup Khanty-Mansiysk 2007 (4.2) 0-1} *

