{We have another typical position from this line, with some small differences.
What's the best continuation for Black now?} 13... Nxe3 (13... Ndf6 $5 {
is also playable}) 14. Qxe3 Bxf1 $1 {[%csl Yc1] Don't forget the king is still
on c1 and Black has not castled yet - this makes things quite a difference.} (
14... Bxb3 $2 15. axb3 O-O $2 {Black is simply one tempo behind now.} 16. Qh6
Bf6 17. Rxd6 $18) 15. Rdxf1 h6 $1 {[%cal Ge7g5] Black can use the king's
placement in his favour too.} 16. Kb1 Bg5 17. Qf2 Rc8 18. Nd5 Nf6 {Black is
fine.} 19. h4 Nxd5 20. hxg5 Nf4 $1 21. gxh6 gxh6 $15 {[%csl Yf4,Gh6] ;
Iljiushenok,I (2427) -Areshchenko,A (2710) Chigorin Memorial 20th 2012 (3) 0-1}
*

